OL,6,FThe CBO prohibits Coleman from acting
OL,7,F"in a manner that causes or is likely
OL,8,Fto cause nuisance, harassment, alarm,
OL,9,For distress to any persons in North
OL,10,FKesteven".
OL,12,FIf the CBO is breached it is
OL,13,Fconsidered a criminal offence and he
OL,14,Fmay be given a custodial sentence. For
OL,15,Fthe most serious offences, this can be
OL,16,Fup to five years.
OL,18,FColeman has been released on court
OL,19,Fbail until his sentencing in January.
